71,0.06932323,0.00925618,-0.05962796,-0.02077594,-0.01936200,0.08148997,0.04625557,0.01165128,-0.04936607,0.10160364,0.03238567,0.02349862,0.04798064,-0.02897838,-0.01239901,0.03662773,0.00376181,-0.06728682,-0.07137704,-0.01462017,0.00270493,0.06037799,-0.01484321,-0.06467094,-0.03562104,-0.05365773,0.01224121,0.01185199,-0.02784382,-0.01855112,-0.07169657,0.04020505,0.03962817,0.00209013,-0.01302214,-0.02136220,0.03105797,0.09139415,0.00006923,0.04120416,0.00309149,0.01932722]',E'Specify outputs in the `@Component` decorator\n\nIn addition to the `@Output` decorator, you can also specify a component''s outputs with the `outputs` property in the `@Component` decorator. This can be useful when a component inherits a property from a base class:\n\n```ts\n// `CustomSlider` inherits the `valueChanged` property from `BaseSlider`.\n@Component({\n  /*...*/\n  outputs: [''valueChanged''],\n})\nexport class CustomSlider extends BaseSlider {}\n```\n\nYou can additionally specify an output alias in the `outputs` list by putting the alias after a colon in the string:\n\n```ts\n// `CustomSlider` inherits the `valueChanged` property from `BaseSlider`.\n@Component({\n  /*...*/\n  outputs: [''valueChanged: volumeChanged''],\n})\nexport class CustomSlider extends BaseSlider {}\n```','{"source": "angular", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Custom events with outputs", "section_title": "outputs", "url": "https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/adev/src/content/guide/components/outputs.md", "topics": "angular,typescript,outputs", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
