52730,0.01264329,0.04320817,0.01075069,-0.03059692,0.07910839,0.02266523,-0.00128653,-0.03643993,0.08637582,-0.00337237,0.02547010,-0.05746579,-0.05882576,0.07118993,-0.01684860,0.01622169,-0.07750035,0.05928746,-0.01010994,-0.00635539,-0.00470128,-0.02043778,-0.07886826,0.02672767,-0.08436306,0.00078558,-0.01695490,0.01212551,0.01424282,-0.05596936,0.02403557,-0.00376182,0.01026479,0.00666810,0.03456619,0.02246848,0.09434345,0.00468996,0.05472643,-0.00664529,0.04264779]',E'Setup in reactive forms\n\nWith reactive forms, you define the form model directly in the component class.\nThe `[formControl]` directive links the explicitly created `FormControl` instance to a specific form element in the view, using an internal value accessor.\n\nThe following component implements an input field for a single control, using reactive forms.\nIn this example, the form model is the `FormControl` instance.\n\n<docs-code language="angular-ts" path="adev/src/content/examples/forms-overview/src/app/reactive/favorite-color/favorite-color.component.ts"/>\n\nIMPORTANT: In reactive forms, the form model is the source of truth; it provides the value and status of the form element at any given point in time, through the `[formControl]` directive on the `<input>` element.','{"source": "angular", "version": "19", "language": "typescript", "title": "Overview", "section_title": "overview", "url": "https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/adev/src/content/guide/forms/overview.md", "topics": "angular,typescript,overview", "categories": "web,typescript,frontend,spa"}');
